      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(codex): return explicit Computer Use approval content",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #96452.\n\nThis changes the Codex app-server MCP elicitation bridge so approved empty-schema approval forms return explicit machine-readable approval content:\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"accept\", \"content\": { \"approve\": true }, \"_meta\": null }\n```\n\nPreviously, empty-schema approvals returned a contentless accept:\n\n```json\n{ \"action\": \"accept\", \"content\": null, \"_meta\": null }\n```\n\nFor Computer Use, that shape can leave the downstream MCP helper with an accepted elicitation but no explicit approval field to consume, matching the issue's symptom where the approval path is crossed and the native `computer-use/get_app_state` call then waits until Codex's 120s `tools/call` timeout.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Returns `{ approve: true }` for approved MCP elicitations whose requested schema has no fields.\n- Keeps deny/cancel behavior unchanged.\n- Keeps unmappable non-empty schemas fail-closed with `decline`.\n- Updates Computer Use approval bridge regressions, including custom server-name, missing-schema, allow-always, sanitization, and empty-schema cases.\n- Documents the Computer Use empty-schema approval response boundary without changing Codex-owned native MCP execution.\n\n## Safety / boundary\n\nThis does not broaden Computer Use permissions or bypass Codex/macOS permission checks. It only changes the OpenClaw approval bridge response from a contentless `accept` to an explicit approval object after the existing OpenClaw approval flow has already produced an allow decision.\n\n## Verification\n\nLocal lightweight checks:\n\n- `git diff --check` — passed.\n\nGitHub Actions focused proof:\n\n- `Issue 96452 Focused Proof` — passed on `snowzlmbot/openclaw` proof branch.\n- Run: https://github.com/snowzlmbot/openclaw/actions/runs/28111159509\n- Command:\n\n```bash\npnpm exec vitest run \\\n  extensions/codex/src/app-server/elicitation-bridge.test.ts \\\n  -t \"Computer Use|empty form schema\"\n```\n\nNote: an earlier proof run failed because two legacy Computer Use assertions still expected `content: null`; those assertions were updated and the final proof above passed.\n\n## Not tested\n\n- Live macOS Discord-routed `computer-use/get_app_state` against Chrome was not rerun from this environment. The focused fix targets the approval response shape visible in OpenClaw source and covered by the bridge tests; Codex still owns the native MCP helper execution after approval.\n",
